{"id":"math140-antideriv210-ia002","cid":"MATH 140","topic":"Integration and Antiderivatives","subtopic":"Antiderivatives — power rule","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"Marginal cost is MC(x) = {a}x^{n}. Find the total cost function TC(x) = integral of MC dx.","params":{"a":{"type":"int","min":2,"max":9},"n":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":3}},"answer_expr":"antideriv210","steps":["TC(x) = integral of {a}x^{n} dx = {answer_antideriv210}x^{new_exp210} + C.","The constant C represents the fixed cost."],"tags":["business-calculus","total-cost","marginal-cost","antiderivative"]}
